      "message": "It\u0027s not needed for any reason except the UNIQUE (name, vlan_id) constraint below. This allows us to enforce per-VLAN hostname uniqueness with one SQL statement. Imagine a user wants to add a VM called \"vm\" to \"physical-host-1\" and another VM also called \"vm\" to \"physical-host-2\". How do we know if this is allowed or not? It\u0027s allowed if physical-host-1 and physical-host-2 are on different VLANs. If vlan_id is not here, then we need some other way to ensure that the name for this VM isn\u0027t being reused on any machine that has the same VLAN ID.",
