      "writtenOn": "2018-01-23T01:56:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For consistency I was actually thinking of machine_id and host_id since none of the other columns have parent_ in their name (e.g. nics refer to their parent by machine_id not parent_machine_id, and every other foreign key also omits parent_: os_id, vlan_id, etc.).\n\nI think that a reader may be confused either way. If a reader sees parent_machine_id and parent_host_id, the reader may expect there to be two parents of different types and for both to be filled in. Comments in relevant places would likely be needed in any case.",
      "parentUuid": "6c6e1381_752a7169",
