      "writtenOn": "2018-01-23T23:42:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think a FK field name must clearly communicate the relationship that the field is representing. So far, \"\u003canother_table_name\u003e_id\" worked well because relationships were obvious:\n\n- vlan_id: VLAN of the host\n- os_id: OS of the host\n- machine_id: machine of the host\n\nThis does not work for host_id: \"the host of the host\". This does not make sense. \"parent_id\" was a bit better, but also not great: what is parent exactly.\n\n\"machine_id\" name with the new meaning is problematic too because it reads as \"machine of the host\", but that\u0027s not true for virtual hosts: they won\u0027t have machine id, although there is definitely machine backing up the vm indirectly.\n\nthe relationships we want to add are:\n- the underlying physical host backing this virtual host\n- the underlying machine *directly* backing this physical host.\n\nlet\u0027s choose field names that clearly communicate these relationships.",
      "parentUuid": "8d50db72_73afa796",
